Description: Two joining fragments of amygdaloid handle from a Knidian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine orange-brown; mixed inclusions. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription and ivy leaf symbol.
Type series: KT601 (Virginia Grace's unpublished K(nidian) T(ype) series)
Curator's comments: Names, Asklepiodoros, Ermokrates. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.55, 3. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0295)
